widget" data-widget_type=3D"text-editor.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<ol data-pm-slice=3D"3 1 []"><li>Identify the numbers for which yo=
u want to find the LCM.</li><li>Look for the smallest common multiple that =
appears in the list for all the numbers.</li><li>Begin by listing the multi=
ples of each number.</li></ol><div>&nbsp;</div><h4>Solved Example On Listin=
g The Multiples Method</h4><p>To determine the least common multiple (LCM) =
of two numbers using a 100 square, you can follow these steps. Let=E2=80=99=
s take the example of finding the LCM of 5 and 7:</p><h5>1. Identify multip=
les of the first number (5)</h5><p>Multiples of 5: 5, 10, 15, 20, 25, 30, 3=
5, =E2=80=A6</p><p><img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" class=3D"alignc=
enter wp-image-8794 size-full" src=3D"https://www.smartick.com/lp/wp-conten=
t/uploads/02-1-1.webp" alt=3D"" width=3D"442" height=3D"442"></p><h5>2. Ide=
ntify multiples of the second number (7)</h5><p>Multiples of 7: 7, 14, 21, =
28, 35, 42, 49, =E2=80=A6</p><h4><img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" c=
lass=3D"aligncenter wp-image-8797 size-full" src=3D"https://www.smartick.co=
m/lp/wp-content/uploads/03-1.webp" alt=3D"" width=3D"439" height=3D"442"></=
h4><h5>3. Find the smallest common multiple</h5><p>Look for numbers that ap=
pear in both lists. In this case, 35 is the smallest number that is a multi=
ple of both 5 and 7.</p><p><img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" class=
=3D"aligncenter wp-image-8800 size-full" src=3D"https://www.smartick.com/lp=
/wp-content/uploads/04-1.webp" alt=3D"" width=3D"439" height=3D"437"></p><p=
><br>Therefore, the LCM of 5 and 7 is 35.</p>								</div>
